t is effortful on developing new laws and structures related to communication and media as well as on resolving the problems in this sector.\n\nPM Dahal appoints NC\u2019s Surendra Acharya as Minister\n\nPrime Minister (PM) Pushpa Kamal Dahal Prachanda has appointed Surendra Acharya of Nepali Congress as a Minister. Prime Minister Dahal appointed Acharya as the Minister of Women, Children and Senior Citizens.\n\nOrdinance tabled in House of Representatives\n\nAn ordinance to amend some Nepal Acts related to the Civil Code, 2080\u2033 has been tabled at the House of Representatives. Minister for Law, Justice and Parliamentary Affairs Dhanraj Gurung tabled the Ordinance in today\u2019s meeting of the House of Representatives. The ordinance was promulgated by the President on May 3.\n\nVabrousek from Czech Republic wins Himalayan Extreme Triathlon title\n\nPetr Vabrousek from Czech Republic won the Himalayan Extreme Triathlon title. In women\u2019s category Tara Miranda Parsons from the United States claimed it. The triathlon considered to be the world\u2019s highest extreme one, started in Pokhara on Saturday morning.\n\nWill end all types of VAW: DPM Shrestha\n\nDeputy Prime Minister and Home Minister Narayan Kaji Shrestha has vowed to end all types of violence against women (VAW). He said the government is committed to take action against the perpetrators of VAW and provide justice to the survivors. The workshop is organised by the Ministry of Home Affairs.\n\nRPP Chairman Lingden asks PM Dahal to investigate all major corruption cases\n\nRastriya Prajatantra Party (RPP) Chairman Rajendra Lingden has asked Prime Minister (PM) Pushpa Kamal Dahal Prachanda to prove his guts by opening files of \u201cmajor corruption\u201d scandals. Speaking at a program in Kathmandu on Sunday, Lingden asked PM Dahal to to open the cases of widebody corruption, Maoist cantonments, etc.\n\nCPN-UML to hold central committee in Kathmandu, not Jhapa\n\nThe CPN-UML has decided to hold its Central Committee meeting in Kathmandu. Earlier, the party had decided to hold the meeting in Jhapa. According to the party, the meeting will be held at UML\u2019s Central Office, Chyasal in Laitpur from May 11-13.\n\nEconomic problems will be resolved through monetary policy: Finance Minister Mahat\n\nFinance Minister Dr Prakash Sharan Mahat has said the current economic problems could be resolved through the monetary policy instead of the fiscal policy. Initiatives would be taken to resolve the problems through the monetary policy as the government lacks options to run the fiscal policy, he said while addressing the Nepal Trade Summit-2023 here today organised by the Confederation of Commercial Banks and Financial Institutions Nepal (CBFIN).\n\n10 Indian nationals arrested for acquiring Nepali citizenship\n\nPolice arrested 10 Indian nationals for obtaining Nepali citizenship certificates. SSP Manoj KC, Head of Kathmandu Valley Crime Investigation Office, said that despite being permanent residents of India\u2019s Uttar Pradesh, they were found to have obtained Nepali citizenship by submitting fake documents.\n\nThree persons dead in Mugu avalanche\n\nThree persons from Patarasi Rural Municipality in Jumla district died in an avalanche occurred on Saturday at Chyarkhu pass of Mugu district. Vice-Chairperson of Patarasi Rural Municipality Jan Maya Rokaya said that Tara Singh Sarki, 40, Purna Sarki, 36, and Bir Bohara, 36, of Talfigaun of Patarasi-2 died in the avalanche.\n\nPresident, PM congratulate King Charles III\n\nPresident Ram Chandra Paudel has sent a message of congratulations to His Majesty King Charles III on His Majesty\u2019s Coronation as the King of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.","title":"Today\u2019s national news in a nutshell","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2023/07/303115/","video":[]}
